{
  "stem": "13079.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And Dad said, if you want any coaching, I'll be glad to pay for that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he said, if you pass that entrance exam, I'll give you $500.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I passed that exam, and I got my 500 bucks and went to New York, and I spent it all before I got to West Point.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had just enough there to pay my railroad fare from Weehawken up to West Point when I entered in July of 1930.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, during your years at West Point, did you anticipate that you were going to be a career military officer, or had you in mind that you might go to law school someday?",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I didn't catch on to becoming a lawyer until my senior year at West Point, where we were required to take a course of law.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was general in nature and was directed primarily toward equipping young officers serving on courts martial as trial judge advocates and defense counsel, and, yeah, that's when I first got a feeling for it.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And during that time, they had to retire as many old officers as there were graduates in my class to make room for 'em, so they invited anybody that wanted to to actually resign and not have to serve as an officer.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I did that after I found out that they would accept me at Harvard.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I went from Harvard-- from West Point to Harvard in September of 1934.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I graduated during the summer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, certainly.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Birkowitz, ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Gilman, ?] two that come to mind in my class.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Absolutely none.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You were your own man in that sense, and we had to go to chapel, and there was a Jewish chapel, and a Catholic chapel, and a Protestant chapel.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were Protestant.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
